issue.title: generate quantization parameter for outputs

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
Histogram based Calibrater doesn't generate quantization parameters for graph outputs.
#11928

body: Same problem here, only MinMax calibration works, either Entropy or Pencentile would yield the same error
The bug was fixed with #12089. Could you please try with nightly build and report back if you still see the issue? Thanks

> The bug was fixed with #12089. Could you please try with nightly build and report back if you still see the issue? Thanks

Thanks for this fix, it works fine with a nightly build!

However I get extremely bad accuracy with entropy calibration. I am going to investigate it a bit more and will create a new issue if needed.

> 

Hi @regisss ,  the accuracy is very bad for entropy calibration on my site too,  did you resolve it ?  thanks

the activation scale factor of the quant model is very large, which would lead bad accuracy.

Hi, @JasonMaojinsong 
I found the same problem when I quantize my model. The range of conv output is very wide, so the scale is very large, e.g. 0.449, so the qdq error is very large because of the large scale factor, which makes the final precision drops a lot.

I wonder what should we do to avoid the presicion lost when we come across big scale factor?
